/// dispatching message objects into their respective handlers
/// (see <b>Advanced Guide to Message Dispatching</b> page of the
/// @b COMMS library documentation), the generated code also provides
/// additional auxiliary dispatch functions which are @b switch statement
/// based.
///
/// The available functions are:
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchMessage
/// (defined in @b mqtt5/dispatch/DispatchMessage.h header file).
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchMessageDefaultOptions
/// (defined in @b mqtt5/dispatch/DispatchMessage.h header file).
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchServerInputMessage
/// (defined in @b mqtt5/dispatch/DispatchServerInputMessage.h header file).
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchServerInputMessageDefaultOptions
/// (defined in @b mqtt5/dispatch/DispatchServerInputMessage.h header file).
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchClientInputMessage
/// (defined in @b mqtt5/dispatch/DispatchClientInputMessage.h header file).
/// @li @ref mqtt5::dispatch::dispatchClientInputMessageDefaultOptions
